


中英文課程綱要









　






招生方式|課表|學分總表|中英文課程綱要 
            



授課計畫表|招生考試考古題|碩博士班 
         
 

碩士班一年級
碩士班二年級
　
　
　



英美侵權行為法專題研究
一年級選（２－０）
希藉英美法院案件解析與相關資料研讀、培養學生法學上思考、分析及判斷能力，瞭解英美侵權行為法律體系及其應用；內容包括：侵權行為民事責任沿革、故意侵權行為、過失侵權行為、因果關係、共同侵權行為、傳來侵權責任、土地所有/占有人責任、嚴格責任、產品製造人責任、誹謗、濫訴、不實陳述、新型態侵權行為、抗辯事由、損害賠償及其他救濟途徑等。
SEMINAR 
          ON ANGLO-AMERICAN LAW OF TORTS
LL.M. first-year elective (2-0)
This course is to use the leading 
          and teachable Anglo-American Torts cases and various legal materials 
          for the students to understand the contemporary law of Torts and incipient 
          trends. The fundamentals that the course offered for include the following: 
          development of tort liability, intentional torts, negligence, causation, 
          joint tortfeasors, limited duty, owner's and occupiers of land, defense, 
          strict liability, products liability, defamation, misuse of legal procedure, 
          misrepresentation, interference with advantageous relationships and 
          damages. The comparative legal studies are also encouraged in this course, 
          the students many take the related Chinese civil codes into comparison. 
          
英美契約法專題研究
一年級 選 (0-2)
希藉英美法院案例解析與相關資料研讀，培養學生思考契約問題與正確解決問題之方法，進而提升法學上思考、分析及判斷能力，瞭解英美契約法體系及統一商法典第二章買賣法；本課程內容包括：契約自由原則、契約之成立、要約承諾之機制、準契約及事實上契約、約因、契約之履行、契約之解釋及顯失公平、違約及其救濟、契約債權債務之轉移、第三人利益契約、誠信原則、口頭證據法則、實質履行法則、條件與期前拒絕等。本課程並採取與我國民法相關規定為比較法研討，得以俾益學生於我國法律之學習。
SEMINAR 
          ON ANGLO-AMERICAN LAW OF CONTRACTS
LL.M. first-year elective (0-2)
The underlying purposes of this 
          course is to teach the students to consider the possible ways of handling 
          a contract problem, and to choose the right way of solving the legal 
          problem. The students use the cases and materials as the learning tool 
          to enhance the thinking and analyzing abilities, especially to learn 
          American contract law which includes the Article two of the Uniform 
          Commercial code. The fundamentals that the course offered for include 
          the following: consideration, bargain principle, remedier, offer and 
          acceptance, quasi-contract and implied-in-fact contracts, bargain in 
          good faith, the parol evidence rule, course of performance, assignment, 
          interpretation and unconsionability, mistake, changed circumstances, 
          third party beneficiaries, performance in good faith, the doctrine of 
          substantial performance, espress conditions, breach and anticipatory 
          speculation. The comparative legal studies are also encouraged in this 
          course, the students may take the related Chinese civil codes into comparison.
比較商事法專題研究（一）（二）
一年級 選（２－０）（０－２）
我國商事法係仿自歐美立法及有關國際公約，由於外文翻譯及立法技術上之疏誤，致法文解釋及實務適用每滋疑義，有賴以比較法學方法，探本溯源，尋求正確答案。本課程之設，當及本此意旨。如進而參考最新國際商事法學思潮，對我國商事法之缺失，提出修正建議則尤所樂見。
SEMINAR 
          ON COMPARATIVE COMMERCIAL LAW（I）（II）
LL.M. first-year elective （2-0）(0-2)
Most of our commercial laws are 
          succeeded from European, American and related international legislation. 
          Therefore, the interpretation as well as the application of the provisions 
          of the commercial laws frequently incur disputes because of the possible 
          faulty translation. The comparative study may bring us back to the Travaux 
          Preparatories of the provisions and help us find out the true meaning 
          of the External Context of the laws. Indeed, this is also the 
          main focus of this course. 
Actually, looking into the trend 
          of the related development might provide us an aid to locate the insufficiency 
          of our temporary legislation. Besides, it is also delightful if an amendment 
          can be derived therefrom.
比較憲法專題研究（一）（二）
一年級 選（2-0）（0-2）
本課程旨在深入研究法治先進各國（如美、英、德、日、法）憲法與本國憲法在構造、學說與判決等方面之異同，以嘗試解決本國憲政發展所遭遇之問題。各學期依研討之主題，定有不同之專題名稱。例如：違憲審查理論、權利分立原則與憲政改革規劃、權利分立原則與違憲審查制度、平等權之發展趨勢、言論自由之理論與實際等。各學期前三分之二為研讀選定教材（含論文與案例），後三分之一課程由選修同學自訂與研討專題相關之題目，撰寫報告，提出課堂討論。
SEMINAR 
          ON COMPARATIVE CONSITITUTION LAW
LL.M. first-year elective （2-0）(0-2)
The aim of the present course 
          is to deeply probe the differences and sameness of the structure, doctrines 
          and judgments of the constitutional laws among US, UK, Germany, Japan, 
          France and ROC. The attempt of this course is to try to solve the problems 
          arising from the process of our domestic constitutional development. 
          The themes of the two terms are given different topics, such as theories 
          of Unconstitutional Review the Principle of separation of Powers and 
          The Reformation Project of Constitution the Principle of Separation 
          of Powers And The Institution Of Unconstitutional Review the Developing 
          Tendency of The Right of Equity, theory And Practice of Freedom of Speech 
          etc. In each term, during the first two thirds of the course, students 
          are requested to read selective materials including legal articles and 
          cases. And during the later one third, students choose their own subjects 
          and write reports accordingly which are related with the present course 
          and fully discussed in class. 
比較刑法專題研究（一）（二）
一年級 選（2-0）（0-2）
本課程係比較法課程，亦即就本國刑法與外國刑法（德國、日本、英美…..）之相關規定，分別設計各個專題，作為分析、比較的授課內容與研究對象。
本課程之目的乃在培養受課者，如何從外國法之規定中，知悉本國法之規定缺陷何在，又如何思索建立本國法應有的體系結構規定。
受課者應具備相關外語能力，則可希望達成本課程之設計目的。
SEMINAR 
          ON COMPARTIVE CRIMINAL LAW（Ⅰ）（Ⅱ）
LL.M. first-year elective（2-0） 
          (0-2)

1.This is a comparative law 
            course. That is, this course will cover selected topics and compare 
            the relevant provisions in the domestic and foreign criminal codes（such 
            as Germany, Japan, the Great Britain, U.S.A….）.
2.The objective of this course 
            is to help the students to understand the defects in the domestic 
            criminal code and to find solution for possible structural improvement, 
            through the study of the foreign legal system.
3.Should the student possess 
            adequate foreign language capability, the objective of this course 
            will be better achieved.

日本法學名著選讀
一年級 選（0-2）
本課程乃藉由閱讀相關日本之法學名著，以增進學生對法學知識之認知，並培養法學研究之能力。
SELECTED 
          READING OF KNOWN JAPAN LAW TREATISEA
LL.M. first-year elective (0-2)
We intent the graduate students 
          can deepen and spread their jurisprudence knowledge by reading the original 
          literature Japanese jurisprudence, and grow up their research ability 
          on jurisprudence.
法學方法論
一年級 選（2-0）
法學方法論旨在探討、詮釋、批判法學理論之所自來，其存在與衍化，科學，技術之運用，及其實踐功能等根本原理，具有哲學先設性、存在衍化性、科學技術行及實踐功能性，故其範疇可分為哲學論、現象論、技術論與實踐論等。
METHODOLOGY 
          OF LEGAL SCIENCE
LL.M. first-year elective（2-0）
Methodology of Legal Science 
          is a course for probing, interpreting and criticizing the theories and 
          doctrines of legal science, including the fundamental principles of 
          their birth, existence, vicissitude, their exercise of scientific methods, 
          and their practical functions. As a result, the province of such discipline 
          may be viewed from philosophical, phenomenal, technical and practical 
          respects.
國際經濟法專題研究（一）
一年級 選（２－０）
本課程著重當前國際經濟之法律問題為研究討論對象，特別涉及世界貿易組織之操作，國家經濟管轄權之域外效力，國際區域經濟組織對全球經濟關係之影響，工業化國家與發展中國家之新國家經濟秩序關係，以及發展中國家主張天然資源之主權等專題乃為當前國際關係之焦點。
SEMINAR 
          ON INTERNATIONAL ECONMIC LAWS（I）
LL.M. first-year elective（2-0）
The course will look deeply into 
          the conflicts between industrialized and less developed countries. The 
          course will specifically address on the development and management of 
          ocean resources, the establishment of new trade relation between wealthy 
          and poor countries, the transferrance of high technology, and the influence 
          of international economic financial institutions to the developing countries.
國際經濟法專題研究（二）
一年級 選（０－２）
本課程深入探討當前工業化國家與非工業化國家在經濟方面之衝突，在特別涉及海洋資源的開發與使用，新國際經濟秩序下如何建立貧富國家間的新貿易關係，技術移轉問題，以及國際經濟財政組織對發展中國家之影響等。
SEMINAR 
          ON INTERNATIONAL ECONMIC LAWS（II）
LL.M. first-year elective（0-2）
國際貿易法專題研究（一）（二）
一年級 選（2-0）（0-2） 
本課程側重當前工業化與發展國家之私法貿易難題，尤以各類型之商品買賣運輸，支付，保險等契約兼顧發展中國家的私權。此外通過國際仲裁與主要貿易國家制度之研究，以進一步析解國際貿易法之問題所在。
SEMINAR 
          ON INTERNATIONAL TRADE LAWS
LL.M. first-year elective（2-0）（0-2）
1.The Seminar is intended to 
          analyze private law trade problems between industrialized and developing 
          countries.
2.The problems concern the rights 
          and obligations of developing countries in international sale of goods, 
          transportation, payment, insurance contracts.
3.International Commercial Arbitration.
4.National Trading system of 
          Major Trading Nations.
英美買賣法專題研究（一）（二）
一年級 選（２－０）（０－２）
第一學期介紹美國商法統一法典 UCC 第二章動產買賣法及各州立法之經過，題材涵蓋 
          Statute of Frauds 'Parol Evidence Rule' Doctrine of Unconcienability 
          等，研究動產買賣法必須瞭解動產買賣法亦適用一般契約法準則，但另訂有專屬動產契約之條文，以適應現代商業活動之需要，案例之討論亦涉及風險承擔的問題。
第二學期討論品質保證問題，對明示、默示、排除條款研究其相關問題，另對買受人或消費者大眾遇有瑕疵之商品，受有損害時，法律規定，受害人得提起違反保證責任之訴、侵權行為之訴或無過失責任之訴，一一予以探討。
SEMINAR 
          ON ANGLO-AMERICAN LAW OF SALES(I)(II)
LL.M. first-year elective（2-0）（0-2）
On basis of law of contracts, 
          this course concentrates on the study of Article 2 (Sales of goods) 
          of Uniform Commercial Code (U.C.C.). Article 2 of U.C.C. regulates sales 
          of goods by statutory provisions, while common law of contracts has 
          been developing for hundreds of years by way of court decisions. The 
          aim of this course is mainly to deal with legal questions related to 
          sales of goods. It also serves the purpose to help those students who 
          intend to further their law study in common law countries someday obtain 
          a general legal knowledge of sales of goods, especially in transnational 
          sales situation.
中共涉外經濟法規研究 (一)(二)
一年級 選 (2-0)(0-2)
中共涉外經濟法規之研究必須植基於大陸地區對經濟法之定義；是以本課程之研究必須始自對大陸地區經濟法源起、體系之介紹，而後本諸大陸地區因改革開放帶來之衝擊，就其社會主義意識形態的觀點來介紹其法律。在內容上，本課程之涵蓋十分廣泛，計有外貿、公安、司法行政、對外經濟與技術合作、經濟特區和沿海經濟開放區、工商行政管理、勞動人事、土地管理、涉外仲裁及華僑和港澳台事務等。惟並非所有內容均會加以講授，而係選擇性的介紹；此係間或配合大陸地區來台訪問之學者的專長所必須作的安排。
Laws 
          and Regulations of The PRC Governing Foreign-Related Matters
LL.M. first-year elective（2-0）（0-2）
The study of the course should 
          start from the definition of the Legal System of P.R.C.’s Economic Law. 
          Therefore, this course will begin with the introduction of the origin 
          and the framework of P.R.C.'s Economic Law. Then, taking the impacts 
          of P.R.C.'s open policy into account, the course will turn to the introduction 
          of P.R.C.'s Economic Law from socialism's perspective. 
The major subjects of the course 
          are relating to Foreign Trade, Public Security, Judicial Administration, 
          Foreign Economic Relations and Technological Cooperation, Special Economic 
          Zones and Coastal Economic Development Zones, Administration for Industry 
          and Commerce, Labor and Personnel Administration, Land Administration, 
          Arbitration involving Foreign Interests and Laws and Regulation on Affairs 
          Concerning Oversea Chinese and Hong Kong and Taiwan. However, not all 
          the subjects will be covered for sure. On the contrary, the courses 
          will be adjusted selectively to fit the specialty of possible visiting 
          PRC scholar who will give the lecture in the class
超國界法律問題研究
一年級 選（２－２）
本課程係以法律問題之「超國界」特性為基礎，研究相關法令與處理程序。此種整合性的研究方法，可避免以往為遷就各別法律學科（如國內法\國外法，公法\私法）之研究界限所造成之不足。國家之間的「超國界法律關係」不外乎是立法、司法、行政管轄權之衝突與合作。而國家要妥善處理此種關係，必須使其涉外法令與實踐符合國際社會之規範。本課程除研究此國際規範之外，更嘗試檢討我國之涉外法令之實際案例，以培養學生對超國界法律問題之處理能力。
The 
          studies on transnational Legal Issues
ll.m. first-year elective（2-2）
The course emphasizes on the 
          studies concerning the “transnationality” of legal issues, including 
          the related legislations and judicial or administrative processes. The 
          integrative approach applied in the course may provide students with 
          an opportunity of cross-subject legal studies, for instances, among 
          domestic \ foreign or public \ private laws. The main themes of transnational 
          legal relations?between different countries include the conflict and 
          cooperation regarding legislation and judicial or administrative jurisdictions.
Every country has to adjust each 
          own foreign related legislations and practices in harmary with international 
          rules or regulations.
In addition study on the related 
          international rules, the course will also focus on the analysis of relevant 
          cases, so as to empower the students with the capacity of solving related 
          issues. 
國際談判實務專題
一年級 選（0-2）
本課程為講授討論並進，就談判方式的演進，談判者應具備的條件，談判的目標，條約與協定，各國談判的模式，談判時應遵守之原則，談判的過程，外交談判與專業談判，媒體與談判予以研討，並對重要國際談判做個案研究。課程結束時同學需繳一份專題研究報告，選擇一項國際談判做過程的敘述及簡評。
SEMINAL 
          ON INTERNATIONAL NRGOTIATION PRACTICE
ll.m. first-year elective（0-2）
The course is conducted by intermittently 
          using lectures and group discussions. The subjects include the evolution 
          of methods of negotiation, the qualifications of a negotiator, the objects 
          of negotiation, treaties and agreements, negotiating methods employed 
          by different countries, rules to be observed in negotiations, the process 
          of negotiation, diplomatic negotiations and other types of negotiation, 
          media and negotiation . In the end a few important cases in international 
          negotiation are being studied. Toward the end of the term, students 
          are required to submit a research paper dealing with a case in international 
          negotiation.


回中英文課程綱要

 

　







